 {"id":"frankenjax-89u","title":"Implement higher-rank tensor dot eval parity","description":"JAX numpy dot supports N-D tensor inputs by contracting lhs last axis with rhs second-to-last axis; if rhs is 1-D, output keeps lhs leading axes. fj-lax eval_dot currently supports only rank combinations up to 2. Generalize tensor-tensor dot for rank >=1 with row-major output shape and focused rank-3 parity tests.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-27T09:12:21.806712950Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-27T09:17:35.509333831Z","closed_at":"2026-04-27T09:17:35.507361628Z","close_reason":"Implemented higher-rank tensor dot evaluation with stacked batch-axis tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
